Note:
BINARY TREE - Generic Tree Foundation Tier 0 Primitive

This file implements an unbalanced binary tree of (Integer value)
nodes. It is the structural foundation reused by RedBlackTree, AVLTree
and BTree for their node layout and traversal primitives.

Node structure (32 bytes):
  offset 0:  value (8 bytes)
  offset 8:  left child pointer (8 bytes)
  offset 16: right child pointer (8 bytes)
  offset 24: parent pointer (8 bytes) - 0 for root

Tree structure (24 bytes):
  offset 0:  root pointer (8 bytes) - 0 if empty
  offset 8:  size (8 bytes)
  offset 16: ordering (1 = BST ordering by value, 0 = unordered)

Traversals provided:
- preorder, inorder, postorder, levelorder (BFS)
Each traversal callback receives (visitor_state, value) - the callback
return value is currently unused but reserved for early-exit (return 0
to stop).

Note: The traversal API exposes two production forms. The callback form
dispatches a function pointer at each visited node using the in-tree
call_indirect primitives (CALL-INDIRECT lowering wave). The "collect
into List" form appends values into a caller-supplied List pointer and
is the form preferred by callers that want a materialized result or
want to avoid per-node call overhead. Both forms are first-class.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/queue.runa" as Q
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/stack.runa" as Stk

Note: ============================================================================
Note: CONSTANTS
Note: ============================================================================

Let BTREE_NODE_SIZE be 32
Let BTREE_HEADER_SIZE be 24
Let BTREE_VALUE_OFFSET be 0
Let BTREE_LEFT_OFFSET be 8
Let BTREE_RIGHT_OFFSET be 16
Let BTREE_PARENT_OFFSET be 24

Note: ============================================================================
Note: NODE PRIMITIVES
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Allocate a single tree node with the given value, no children, no
parent. Caller links it into the tree.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 32 bytes, set value, set three pointer fields to 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: 32 bytes per node.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_node_create" takes value as Integer returns Integer:
    Let node be proc allocate from Layout with BTREE_NODE_SIZE
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_VALUE_OFFSET, value
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_LEFT_OFFSET, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_RIGHT_OFFSET, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_PARENT_OFFSET, 0
    Return node
End Process

@Reasoning
Field accessors for value, left, right, parent. Exposed as procs so
external types (RB, AVL) can build their own augmented layouts and
still read core BinaryTree fields via these names.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Single memory_get_int64 at the canonical offset.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_node_value" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_VALUE_OFFSET
End Process

@Reasoning
Left-child accessor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
memory_get_int64 at left offset.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_node_left" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_LEFT_OFFSET
End Process

@Reasoning
Right-child accessor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
memory_get_int64 at right offset.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_node_right" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_RIGHT_OFFSET
End Process

@Reasoning
Parent accessor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
memory_get_int64 at parent offset.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_node_parent" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
