End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TREE CONSTRUCTION / DESTRUCTION
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Create an empty tree.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate 24-byte header; root = 0, size = 0, ordering = 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_tree_create" returns Integer:
    Let tree be proc allocate from Layout with BTREE_HEADER_SIZE
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 0, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 8, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 16, 0
    Return tree
End Process

@Reasoning
Create an empty BST. Identical layout to binary_tree_create but flags
the ordering bit so insertion methods know to maintain the BST property.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Calls binary_tree_create then sets ordering = 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_tree_create_bst" returns Integer:
    Let tree be proc binary_tree_create
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 16, 1
    Return tree
End Process

@Reasoning
Free the entire tree iteratively. Recursion would risk stack overflow
for adversarial inputs (a left-spine tree of depth n). An explicit
stack of node pointers bounds memory use to O(depth) and runs in O(n).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Use a Stack of node pointers. Push root. Loop: pop, push non-zero
left and right children, then free the popped node.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(depth) worst case = O(n) for a skewed tree.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Iterative to avoid stack overflow on adversarial depth.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_tree_destroy" takes tree as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    If root is not equal to 0:
        Let stk be proc stack_create from Stk
        If stk is equal to 0:
            Note: Best-effort: if stack allocation fails, leak the nodes
            Note: rather than corrupt state. The caller's process exit will
            Note: reclaim heap, and partial freeing would leave dangling
            Note: parent pointers that destruction-time canary checks would
            Note: flag as use-after-free during quarantine eviction.
            proc deallocate from Layout with tree
            Return 0
        End If
        proc stack_push from Stk with stk, root
        While 1 is equal to 1:
            Let empty be proc stack_is_empty from Stk with stk
            If empty is equal to 1:
                Return 0 minus 0
            End If
            Let node be proc stack_pop from Stk with stk
            Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_LEFT_OFFSET
            Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_RIGHT_OFFSET
            If left is not equal to 0:
                proc stack_push from Stk with stk, left
            End If
            If right is not equal to 0:
                proc stack_push from Stk with stk, right
            End If
            proc deallocate from Layout with node
            Let still_empty be proc stack_is_empty from Stk with stk
            If still_empty is equal to 1:
                proc stack_destroy from Stk with stk
                proc deallocate from Layout with tree
                Return 1
            End If
        End While
    End If
    proc deallocate from Layout with tree
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Tree size accessor.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
memory_get_int64 at offset 8.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_tree_size" takes tree as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 8
End Process

@Reasoning
Empty predicate.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Returns 1 if root pointer is 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_tree_is_empty" takes tree as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: BST INSERT / SEARCH
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Insert value into the tree maintaining BST ordering. Duplicates go
into the left subtree by convention (so in-order yields a stable
sorted order including duplicates).
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) If root is 0, allocate node, set as root, size = 1.
2) Else walk: at each node compare value < / > / <= node.value;
   descend left if value <= node.value, right if value > node.value.
3) When the chosen child pointer is 0, allocate node, link as child,
   set parent.
4) Increment size.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(h) where h is current height. Worst-case O(n) for skewed
inputs - use RedBlackTree or AVLTree if balance is required.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_tree_insert" takes tree as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    If root is equal to 0:
        Let node be proc binary_node_create with value
        If node is equal to 0:
            Return 0
        End If
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 0, node
        proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 8, 1
        Return 1
    End If
    Let cur be root
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let cv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, BTREE_VALUE_OFFSET
        If value is less than or equal to cv:
            Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, BTREE_LEFT_OFFSET
            If left is equal to 0:
                Let new_node be proc binary_node_create with value
                If new_node is equal to 0:
                    Return 0
                End If
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with new_node, BTREE_PARENT_OFFSET, cur
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cur, BTREE_LEFT_OFFSET, new_node
                Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 8
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 8, size plus 1
                Return 1
            End If
            Set cur to left
        Otherwise:
            Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, BTREE_RIGHT_OFFSET
            If right is equal to 0:
                Let new_node be proc binary_node_create with value
                If new_node is equal to 0:
                    Return 0
                End If
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with new_node, BTREE_PARENT_OFFSET, cur
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with cur, BTREE_RIGHT_OFFSET, new_node
                Let size be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 8
                proc memory_set_int64 from Memory with tree, 8, size plus 1
                Return 1
            End If
            Set cur to right
        End If
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Find node pointer with matching value, or 0 if absent. Standard BST
descent.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Walk from root, descending left or right based on comparison.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(h). Space: O(1) (iterative).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_tree_find" takes tree as Integer, value as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    While cur is not equal to 0:
        Let cv be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, BTREE_VALUE_OFFSET
        If value is equal to cv:
            Return cur
        End If
        If value is less than cv:
            Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, BTREE_LEFT_OFFSET
        Otherwise:
            Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, BTREE_RIGHT_OFFSET
        End If
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: TRAVERSALS - collect into a List
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Pre-order traversal: visit node, then left subtree, then right subtree.
Appends values into a caller-supplied List in pre-order.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Iterative with an explicit stack. Push root. Loop: pop node, append
its value, push right child (if any), push left child (if any). The
push-right-before-left ordering means left is processed first.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(h) for the stack.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure of the helper stack.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_tree_preorder" takes tree as Integer, out_list as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If out_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let stk be proc stack_create from Stk
    If stk is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc stack_push from Stk with stk, root
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let empty be proc stack_is_empty from Stk with stk
        If empty is equal to 1:
            proc stack_destroy from Stk with stk
            Return 1
        End If
        Let node be proc stack_pop from Stk with stk
        Let v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_VALUE_OFFSET
        proc list_append from List with out_list, v
        Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_RIGHT_OFFSET
        Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_LEFT_OFFSET
        If right is not equal to 0:
            proc stack_push from Stk with stk, right
        End If
        If left is not equal to 0:
            proc stack_push from Stk with stk, left
        End If
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
In-order traversal: left subtree, node, right subtree. For a BST the
in-order traversal yields the values in sorted order, which is a
critical correctness check used by the RB and AVL test suites.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Morris-style traversal would use O(1) space but requires temporary
thread mutation of right pointers. Use the simpler O(h) stack approach
for clarity and predictability.

Loop:
- Walk left from cur, pushing each node onto the stack.
- When cur is 0, pop, append value, then set cur = popped.right.
- Terminate when both cur and stack are exhausted.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(h) stack.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_tree_inorder" takes tree as Integer, out_list as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If out_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let stk be proc stack_create from Stk
    If stk is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        While cur is not equal to 0:
            proc stack_push from Stk with stk, cur
            Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, BTREE_LEFT_OFFSET
        End While
        Let empty be proc stack_is_empty from Stk with stk
        If empty is equal to 1:
            proc stack_destroy from Stk with stk
            Return 1
        End If
        Let node be proc stack_pop from Stk with stk
        Let v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_VALUE_OFFSET
        proc list_append from List with out_list, v
        Set cur to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_RIGHT_OFFSET
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Post-order traversal: left subtree, right subtree, node. Two-stack
algorithm: traverse modified pre-order pushing onto a second stack,
then drain the second stack as the post-order result.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Stack A starts with root. Loop:
- Pop a node from A.
- Push it onto stack B.
- Push left then right onto A (reverse of preorder so B receives
  right-then-left, which reverses to left-then-right-then-node = post).
After A is empty, pop everything from B into out_list.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n) for the two stacks combined.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_tree_postorder" takes tree as Integer, out_list as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If out_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let a be proc stack_create from Stk
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let b be proc stack_create from Stk
    If b is equal to 0:
        proc stack_destroy from Stk with a
        Return 0
    End If
    proc stack_push from Stk with a, root
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let empty be proc stack_is_empty from Stk with a
        If empty is equal to 1:
            Note: drain b
            While 1 is equal to 1:
                Let b_empty be proc stack_is_empty from Stk with b
                If b_empty is equal to 1:
                    proc stack_destroy from Stk with a
                    proc stack_destroy from Stk with b
                    Return 1
                End If
                Let node be proc stack_pop from Stk with b
                Let v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_VALUE_OFFSET
                proc list_append from List with out_list, v
            End While
        End If
        Let n be proc stack_pop from Stk with a
        proc stack_push from Stk with b, n
        Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with n, BTREE_LEFT_OFFSET
        Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with n, BTREE_RIGHT_OFFSET
        If left is not equal to 0:
            proc stack_push from Stk with a, left
        End If
        If right is not equal to 0:
            proc stack_push from Stk with a, right
        End If
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

@Reasoning
Level-order (BFS) traversal: visit nodes by depth, left-to-right within
each depth. Uses a queue.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Queue starts with root. Loop: dequeue, append value, enqueue left and
right children. Terminate when queue empties.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(w) where w is the maximum width = O(n/2) at the
last level of a balanced tree.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on allocation failure of the queue.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_tree_levelorder" takes tree as Integer, out_list as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If out_list is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let q be proc queue_create from Q
    If q is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc queue_enqueue from Q with q, root
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let empty be proc queue_is_empty from Q with q
        If empty is equal to 1:
            proc queue_destroy from Q with q
            Return 1
        End If
        Let node be proc queue_dequeue from Q with q
        Let v be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_VALUE_OFFSET
        proc list_append from List with out_list, v
        Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_LEFT_OFFSET
        Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_RIGHT_OFFSET
        If left is not equal to 0:
            proc queue_enqueue from Q with q, left
        End If
        If right is not equal to 0:
            proc queue_enqueue from Q with q, right
        End If
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: MIN / MAX / SUCCESSOR / PREDECESSOR (BST)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Walk left until no more left children to find the minimum-keyed node.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
From the supplied subtree root, follow left pointers; return last
non-null. Returns 0 if subtree is empty.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(h).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_tree_subtree_min" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be node
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, BTREE_LEFT_OFFSET
        If left is equal to 0:
            Return cur
        End If
        Set cur to left
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Walk right until no right children to find the maximum-keyed node.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Mirror of subtree_min.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(h).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_tree_subtree_max" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let cur be node
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, BTREE_RIGHT_OFFSET
        If right is equal to 0:
            Return cur
        End If
        Set cur to right
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
In-order successor: smallest node in right subtree if it exists,
otherwise walk up the parent chain until we come from a left child.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
1) If node.right is non-zero, return subtree_min(node.right).
2) Otherwise walk parent chain: cur = node, p = node.parent. While p
   is non-zero and cur == p.right, cur = p, p = p.parent. Return p.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(h).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_tree_successor" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_RIGHT_OFFSET
    If right is not equal to 0:
        Return proc binary_tree_subtree_min with right
    End If
    Let cur be node
    Let p be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, BTREE_PARENT_OFFSET
    While p is not equal to 0:
        Let p_right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, BTREE_RIGHT_OFFSET
        If cur is not equal to p_right:
            Return p
        End If
        Set cur to p
        Set p to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, BTREE_PARENT_OFFSET
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
In-order predecessor: largest node in left subtree if any, otherwise
walk up until we come from a right child.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Mirror of successor.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(h).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Read-only.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_tree_predecessor" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_LEFT_OFFSET
    If left is not equal to 0:
        Return proc binary_tree_subtree_max with left
    End If
    Let cur be node
    Let p be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with cur, BTREE_PARENT_OFFSET
    While p is not equal to 0:
        Let p_left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, BTREE_LEFT_OFFSET
        If cur is not equal to p_left:
            Return p
        End If
        Set cur to p
        Set p to proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with p, BTREE_PARENT_OFFSET
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: HEIGHT
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Compute tree height iteratively using a queue and a small bookkeeping
loop (BFS layer count). Avoids the recursion-depth pitfall that would
otherwise track stack frames proportional to height.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
BFS by layer: for each layer count the nodes currently in queue, then
process exactly that many nodes (each enqueueing its children).
Increment height by 1 per layer. Empty tree -> 0; one-node tree -> 1.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(w).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Returns 0 on null tree or allocation failure.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "binary_tree_height" takes tree as Integer returns Integer:
    If tree is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let root be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with tree, 0
    If root is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let q be proc queue_create from Q
    If q is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    proc queue_enqueue from Q with q, root
    Let height be 0
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let layer_count be proc queue_count from Q with q
        If layer_count is equal to 0:
            proc queue_destroy from Q with q
            Return height
        End If
        Set height to height plus 1
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than layer_count:
            Let node be proc queue_dequeue from Q with q
            Let left be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_LEFT_OFFSET
            Let right be proc memory_get_int64 from Memory with node, BTREE_RIGHT_OFFSET
            If left is not equal to 0:
                proc queue_enqueue from Q with q, left
            End If
            If right is not equal to 0:
                proc queue_enqueue from Q with q, right
            End If
            Set i to i plus 1
        End While
    End While
    Return height
End Process
